  "title" : "How to capitalize the first letter of word in a string using Java?",
  "body" : "<p>Example strings</p>\n\n<pre><code>one thousand only\ntwo hundred\ntwenty\nseven\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>How do I change the first character of a string in capital letter and not change the case of any of the other letters?</p>\n\n<p>After the change it should be:</p>\n\n<pre><code>One thousand only\nTwo hundred\nTwenty\nSeven\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note: I don't want to use the apache.commons.lang.WordUtils to do this.</p>\n"
